{#- Single canonical advisory-list rendering used by:
      * dashboard open-positions list-view row (open_positions_row.html.j2)
      * open-positions expanded fragment (open_positions_expanded.html.j2)
      * trade-detail page Advisories section (trades/detail.html.j2)

    Contract: caller passes `advisories` (tuple[AdvisorySuggestionVM, ...])
    via `{% with advisories = ... %}` (mirrors the dashboard's existing
    `{% for s in row.advisories %}` pattern).

    NO empty-state markup here — empty-state handling is per-surface so the
    list-view cell and the detail-page section can differ (the list view
    leaves the cell empty; the detail page renders "No advisories." in the
    `{% else %}` branch around the include).

    CLAUDE.md gotcha — "HTMX OOB-swap partials that hand-duplicate full-page
    markup drift silently." This partial IS the canonical rendering target;
    do NOT inline-duplicate `<div>{{ s.message }}</div>` in any caller. -#}
{% for s in advisories %}
  <div class="advisory">{{ s.message }}</div>
{% endfor %}
